extends layout

block content
  .jumbotron
    p.lead
      | TweetPNG.com provides a super-simple API to display your latest tweet as an image.
  .row.marketing
    h2 How to do it...
    h3.text-center Please Note: This only works with the new <a href="https://about.twitter.com/products/new-profiles">Twitter Profiles</a>.

    h3 Getting your last tweet
    span!= marked("Add `http://www.tweetpng.com/:username/tweet/last.png` to your `img` tag in your HTML, where `:username` is your Twitter handle.")
    p Example:
    p.text-center
      img(src='/joshfinnie/tweet/last.png', alt='')

    h3 Getting your latest tweet including replies
    span!= marked("Add `http://www.tweetpng.com/:username/tweet/last.png?withReplies=true` to your `img` tag in your HTML, where `:username` is your Twitter handle.")
    p Example:
    p.text-center
      img(src='/joshfinnie/tweet/last.png?withReplies=true', alt='')

    h3 Getting a specific tweet
    span!= marked("Add `http://www.tweetpng.com/:username/tweet/:tweetID.png` to your `img` tag in your HTML, where `:username` is your Twitter handle and `:tweetID` in the tweet ID.")
    p Example:
    p.text-center
      img(src='/joshfinnie/tweet/354761173800976384.png', alt='')
